{"lemma":"طَلِيقٌ","slug":"طَلِيقٌ","root":"ط.ل.ق","root_slug":"ط-ل-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-ل-ق","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26984"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%82%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"let loose, not constrained","tags":["general"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"eloquent (when used with لِسَان (lisān))","examples":[{"text":"طَلِيق اللِّسَان","english":"eloquent"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"cheerful (when used with وَجْه (wajh))","examples":[{"text":"طَلِيق الوَجْه","english":"having a cheerful face"},{"text":"لا تَحقِرَنَّ مِنَ المَعْرُوف شَيْئًا، وَلَو أنْ تَلقَى أخَاكَ بوجهٍ طليقٍ","english":"Do not belittle any good deed, even your meeting with your brother with a cheerful face"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"free (element) (not combined with or bonded to other elements.)","examples":[{"text":"عُنْصُر طَلِيق","english":"a free element"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"released, freed (prisoner)","examples":[{"text":"اذْهَبُوا فَأَنْتُمْ الطُّلَقَاءُ","english":"Go, you are free"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"divorcee (of someone)","examples":[{"text":"طَلِيقَة عَمْرْو دِيَاب","english":"Amr Diab's divorcee"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb طَلُقَ (ṭaluqa, “to set loose”)."},"ipa":["/tˤa.liːq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26984","headword_ar":"طَلِيقٌ","root":"Tlq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A captive"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having his bond loosed from him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and let go."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloqN","text_ar":"طَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence. ―         -b2-  And (assumed tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"freed from slavery; emancipated; i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EatiyqN","text_ar":"عَتِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who has become free:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TulaqaA='u","text_ar":"طُلَقَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~ulaqaA='u mino qurayo$K waAlEutaqaA='u mino vaqiyfK","text_ar":"الطُّلَقَا=ءُ مِنْ قُرَيْشٍ وَالعُتَقَا=ءُ مِنْ ثَقِيفٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TulaqaA='","text_ar":"طُلَقَا=ء"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are of Kureysh; and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EutaqaA='","text_ar":"عُتَقَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Thakeef"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlTlqA'","text_ar":"الطلقاء"},{"kind":"text","text":"being app. applied to Kureysh as it has a more special signification than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEtqA'","text_ar":"العتقاء"},{"kind":"text","text":": but accord. to Th,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~ulaqaA='u","text_ar":"الطُّلَقَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those who have been brought within the pale of El-Islám against their will."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taliyqu All~isaAni","text_ar":"طَلِيقُ اللِّسَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lisaAnN TaliyqN *aliyqN","text_ar":"لِسَانٌ طَلِيقٌ ذَلِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b5-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taliyqu Alyadayoni","text_ar":"طَلِيقُ اليَدَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b6-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taliyqu Alwajohi","text_ar":"طَلِيقُ الوَجْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloqN","text_ar":"طَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"again; the last in two places. ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taliyqu AlA_il`hi","text_ar":"طَلِيقُ الاـِلٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}